        {
            "@id": "webuild:concept-109",
            "term:orderedRelated": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-6005"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNote": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "Core characteristics for a legal person:\n- A legal person is created through a legal act (registration, statute, treaty)\n- It has a separate legal personality\n- It acts through representatives\n- It has continuity beyond individual members\n\nTypical narrower concepts:\n- Company / Corporation\n- Association\n- Foundation\n- Cooperative\n- Public authority (NB: public bodies may be legal persons depending on national law)\n- International organisation"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedBroader": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-1"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "suomi-meta:publicationStatus": {
                "@id": "http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT"
            },
            "suomi-meta:modifier": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8",
            "suomi-meta:creator": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8",
            "skos:related": [
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-6005"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                }
            ],
            "skos:prefLabel": {
                "@id": "urn:uuid:c94fbb43-9e60-49fb-8fea-452995505450"
            },
            "skos:note": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "Core characteristics for a legal person:\n- A legal person is created through a legal act (registration, statute, treaty)\n- It has a separate legal personality\n- It acts through representatives\n- It has continuity beyond individual members\n\nTypical narrower concepts:\n- Company / Corporation\n- Association\n- Foundation\n- Cooperative\n- Public authority (NB: public bodies may be legal persons depending on national law)\n- International organisation"
            },
            "skos:inScheme": {
                "@id": "https://iri.suomi.fi/terminology/webuild/"
            },
            "skos:definition": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "an entity other than a natural person that is recognised by law as having legal personality, enabling it to hold rights and obligations independently of the natural persons associated with it"
            },
            "skos:broader": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-1"
            },
            "dcterms:modified": {
                "@value": "2026-01-23T15:05:31.732Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "dcterms:created": {
                "@value": "2026-01-07T10:43:28.799Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "@type": "skos:Concept"
        },
        {
            "@id": "webuild:concept-6006",
            "term:orderedRelated": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-6005"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-105"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-7"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNote": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "In the WE BUILD context a \"legal entity\" is a company, business, sole trader, non-profit association or similar entity that is registered with a business registration authority or other public authority; most \"economic operators\" are therefore also \"legal entities\"."
                    },
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "In WE BUILD, “legal entity” is intended as the transactional/legal identity used in B2B/B2G processes. It can include: a legal person (e.g., company), and in jurisdictions where applicable, a natural person acting as a registered business actor (e.g., sole trader) whose business identity is legally recognised and identifiable."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNarrower": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-98"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedBroader": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "suomi-meta:publicationStatus": {
                "@id": "http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT"
            },
            "suomi-meta:modifier": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8",
            "suomi-meta:creator": "4c00fd3e-ad5d-4ad6-8782-de29597a5d57",
            "skos:related": [
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-6005"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-7"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-105"
                }
            ],
            "@type": "skos:Concept",
            "dcterms:created": "2023-11-09T13:34:04Z",
            "dcterms:modified": {
                "@value": "2026-01-23T14:38:10.967Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "http://purl.org/termed/properties/id": "42ea77c6-99e7-44fd-91b4-33a2f179018d",
            "skos:broader": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
            },
            "skos:changeNote": "alternative definitions:\n1. \"a natural person or a legal person that is recognised by a legal system as capable of holding rights and obligations\"\n2. \"a formal organization that is involved in economic activity\"",
            "skos:definition": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "an agent whose identity is legally recognised for transactions and that can be referenced unambiguously by a legal identifier issued or recognised by a competent authority"
            },
            "skos:inScheme": {
                "@id": "https://iri.suomi.fi/terminology/webuild/"
            },
            "skos:narrower": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-98"
            },
            "skos:note": [
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "In WE BUILD, “legal entity” is intended as the transactional/legal identity used in B2B/B2G processes. It can include: a legal person (e.g., company), and in jurisdictions where applicable, a natural person acting as a registered business actor (e.g., sole trader) whose business identity is legally recognised and identifiable."
                },
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "In the WE BUILD context a \"legal entity\" is a company, business, sole trader, non-profit association or similar entity that is registered with a business registration authority or other public authority; most \"economic operators\" are therefore also \"legal entities\"."
                }
            ],
            "skos:prefLabel": {
                "@id": "urn:uuid:2eaee03b-3e77-4da9-8afd-2f29361a1080"
            }
        },
        {
            "@id": "webuild:concept-105",
            "term:orderedSynonym": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:602507ce-5a2f-42c5-ac2b-294a26b18096"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:75da39c3-ad77-443b-b21e-634e2c61aa34"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:ba8b6757-41f0-4bfb-a3db-947fca50b8ae"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedRelated": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-6006"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-14"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNote": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "The EU Core Business Vocabulary defines \"legal name\" as:\n\"The name under which the Legal Entity is legally registered.\""
                    },
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "The legal name is the authoritative registered/recorded name for legal and regulated contexts; it may differ from trading name(s); it may also have multilingual forms."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedBroader": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-18"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "suomi-meta:publicationStatus": {
                "@id": "http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT"
            },
            "@type": "skos:Concept",
            "dcterms:created": {
                "@value": "2025-01-09T12:45:32.29Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "dcterms:modified": {
                "@value": "2026-04-14T07:13:05.804Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "skos:altLabel": [
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:602507ce-5a2f-42c5-ac2b-294a26b18096"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:75da39c3-ad77-443b-b21e-634e2c61aa34"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:ba8b6757-41f0-4bfb-a3db-947fca50b8ae"
                }
            ],
            "skos:broader": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-18"
            },
            "skos:definition": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "a name under which the legal entity is registered"
            },
            "skos:inScheme": {
                "@id": "https://iri.suomi.fi/terminology/webuild/"
            },
            "skos:note": [
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "The EU Core Business Vocabulary defines \"legal name\" as:\n\"The name under which the Legal Entity is legally registered.\""
                },
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "The legal name is the authoritative registered/recorded name for legal and regulated contexts; it may differ from trading name(s); it may also have multilingual forms."
                }
            ],
            "skos:prefLabel": {
                "@id": "urn:uuid:366211ea-ba2d-4b7d-b633-d7a6097c9c2d"
            },
            "skos:related": [
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-6006"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-14"
                }
            ],
            "suomi-meta:creator": "4c00fd3e-ad5d-4ad6-8782-de29597a5d57",
            "suomi-meta:modifier": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8"
        },
        {
            "@id": "webuild:concept-1",
            "term:orderedSynonym": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:1ac1d898-b700-4b96-9ce7-ca5046703b90"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNote": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "Represents a collection of people organized together into a community or other social, commercial or political structure. The group has some common purpose or reason for existence which goes beyond the set of people belonging to it and can act as an agent. Organizations are often decomposable into hierarchical structures."
                    },
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "Note: an \"organisation\" may or may not have legal personality; \"legal person\" is the “organisation with legal personality” case."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNarrower": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedBroader": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "suomi-meta:publicationStatus": {
                "@id": "http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT"
            },
            "suomi-meta:modifier": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8",
            "@type": "skos:Concept",
            "dcterms:created": "2021-12-13T13:59:08Z",
            "dcterms:modified": {
                "@value": "2026-03-03T06:04:55.903Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "http://purl.org/termed/properties/id": "56d706ed-7a7e-4a2f-9640-28282dd65f7f",
            "skos:altLabel": {
                "@id": "urn:uuid:1ac1d898-b700-4b96-9ce7-ca5046703b90"
            },
            "skos:broader": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
            },
            "skos:changeNote": "alternative definitions:\n\"a structured group of natural persons or legal persons that is formed to achieve specific objectives, operating according to defined roles, rules, and processes\"\n\"a structured group or arrangement with a defined purpose and governance, capable of acting as an actor in processes\"",
            "skos:definition": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "a structured arrangement of one or more persons (natural or legal) created to pursue objectives, with roles and rules that enable it to act"
            },
            "skos:inScheme": {
                "@id": "https://iri.suomi.fi/terminology/webuild/"
            },
            "skos:narrower": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
            },
            "skos:note": [
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "Represents a collection of people organized together into a community or other social, commercial or political structure. The group has some common purpose or reason for existence which goes beyond the set of people belonging to it and can act as an agent. Organizations are often decomposable into hierarchical structures."
                },
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "Note: an \"organisation\" may or may not have legal personality; \"legal person\" is the “organisation with legal personality” case."
                }
            ],
            "skos:prefLabel": [
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:098a4f27-8a45-4d15-bf71-11a1b39ebf8e"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:4e8fa96a-a06b-403a-9d40-8a9a6895841c"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:409042a0-9a8c-4f6b-b314-53b686faedef"
                }
            ],
            "suomi-meta:creator": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8"
        },
        {
            "@id": "webuild:concept-6005",
            "term:orderedSynonym": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:1745f367-be49-46e2-912d-52ceb818d72b"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "urn:uuid:3a9a7dda-073a-4520-b699-8bdf5534bc23"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedRelated": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
                    },
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedNote": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "A natural person exists independently of registration, but her/his legal capacity may be restricted (minor, guardianship, incapacity). \n\nA natural person can act\n- in a private capacity or\n- in a professional or economic capacity (sole trader, freelancer, craftsman, farmer)\n\nA natural person does not cease to be a natural person when conducting business. Economic activity does not transform the person into a legal person, but the natural person can then be considered an economic operator."
                    },
                    {
                        "@language": "en",
                        "@value": "A natural person exists independently of registration. A natural person may act in a private capacity or in a professional/economic capacity (e.g., sole trader). Acting economically does not transform the person into a legal person; it expresses the economic operator capacity."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "term:orderedBroader": {
                "@list": [
                    {
                        "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "suomi-meta:publicationStatus": {
                "@id": "http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT"
            },
            "suomi-meta:modifier": "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8",
            "@type": "skos:Concept",
            "dcterms:created": "2023-11-09T13:22:34Z",
            "dcterms:modified": {
                "@value": "2026-01-23T14:35:37.069Z",
                "@type": "xsd:dateTime"
            },
            "http://purl.org/termed/properties/id": "e0c8e09b-5707-412a-ba06-511d77a5f769",
            "skos:altLabel": [
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:1745f367-be49-46e2-912d-52ceb818d72b"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "urn:uuid:3a9a7dda-073a-4520-b699-8bdf5534bc23"
                }
            ],
            "skos:broader": {
                "@id": "webuild:concept-41"
            },
            "skos:changeNote": "alternative definition:\n\"an individual human being who may be dead or alive, but not imaginary\"",
            "skos:definition": {
                "@language": "en",
                "@value": "a human being recognized by law as an individual subject of rights and obligations"
            },
            "skos:inScheme": {
                "@id": "https://iri.suomi.fi/terminology/webuild/"
            },
            "skos:note": [
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "A natural person exists independently of registration, but her/his legal capacity may be restricted (minor, guardianship, incapacity). \n\nA natural person can act\n- in a private capacity or\n- in a professional or economic capacity (sole trader, freelancer, craftsman, farmer)\n\nA natural person does not cease to be a natural person when conducting business. Economic activity does not transform the person into a legal person, but the natural person can then be considered an economic operator."
                },
                {
                    "@language": "en",
                    "@value": "A natural person exists independently of registration. A natural person may act in a private capacity or in a professional/economic capacity (e.g., sole trader). Acting economically does not transform the person into a legal person; it expresses the economic operator capacity."
                }
            ],
            "skos:prefLabel": {
                "@id": "urn:uuid:d415b619-215c-44cc-b893-cab5df27b067"
            },
            "skos:related": [
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-94"
                },
                {
                    "@id": "webuild:concept-109"
                }
            ],
            "suomi-meta:creator": "4c00fd3e-ad5d-4ad6-8782-de29597a5d57"
        },
